snippet.textDisplay:
Coke Studio Bangla has been mislabeling all of its subtitles since the beginning. 
In all of the songs, the subtitle reads 'Bangla', while it has both Bangla and English. I have seen some international reviewers becoming confused by the issue. One reviewer even opted for secondary auto-translation of the original subtitle to English, which was garbage and very painful to see. 
In my opinion, ideally you should embed the subtitles to the video itself so nobody has to 'turn it on'. In this way, you can reach to the max number of international audience, which I think Coke Studio aims to do. If you don't embed the subtitles, at least get the labels right. Label the mixed subs as 'Bangla-English', or upload Bangla and English subs separate. 
It is such a basic management issue and can be fixed easily. Honestly I would be harsh enough to call it sloppy and negligent management. 
If someone has access to Coke Studio Bangla, please let them know of the issue. Hope they will fix it soon.
